title: For Sale:  Colt Single Action Army Revolver SAA Gold, Frontier Six Shooter, Ivory Grips c.1925, Cased
postcontent:
This is a unique and extremely rare Colt Single Action Army revolver, in .44-40 caliber, which is factory gold plated with factory ivory grips, made in 1925 (serial #347526). It was originally shipped to G. W. Shroyer and Company, Dayton, Ohio, May 16, ’25, as a blue and case colored .32-20 with 7.5” barrel. It was returned to the Colt plant sometime between then and 1937, when it was changed to a Frontier Six Shooter (.44-40) with 5.5” barrel, ivory grips with medallions, and gold plated, as evidenced by the Colt rework “&” (ampersand) mark on the right rear of the trigger guard. It appears unfired since the factory rework.

As Kopec states in his book (p. 169, 1976 edition), “… in most parts of the world the SA’s hard working days were over, and … a number of its sales after 1923 were intended as gifts, presentations, prizes or just to rekindle memories of the ‘good old days.’…” This Colt typifies guns of that nature, remaining in 95% plus condition, with only the gold having been rubbed off in spots. The nickel finish, where the gold is missing, is almost perfect (gold plated guns had to be nickel plated before the gold would adhere).

This fine Colt has been custom cased in a late 1800’s lap desk, made of hardwoods and intricate inlaid veneers. It comes with the revolver’s accessories as well as antique pen, nibs and brass ink well holders. The case also has its key and locks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Beware: Texas has the most scammer ads of all the States!
location: All of Texas, Texas, United States
postcontent:
Before you send money or trades DEMAND another picture with a specified object placed next to it like a (water glass) to validate the seller has the item being offered. If it's a scam, you'll get flimsy excuses but no picture.
Copy and search using sites like Start Page, Bing, Google, etc. will most often find the ad where the picture and description were stolen.
Also use the search box in the upper right corner of this page for e-mail addresses and items with similar names for example "Colt Python" see if the same ad/picture/seller appears in another State.
Lastly, If someone's smart enough to place an ad here, he's got to be smart enough to figure out what his gun's worth; You're not going to buy a $1,500 Colt for $750. I don't care how desperate they are. The scammers don't have a nickel into it, so ANY money you send is theirs and gone!
Be smart, give it more than a once over, think before firing off an I'll take it e-mail because you think you've hit a home run because you'll be thrown out before reaching first base.

title: For Sale:  Intermediate Pistol Class on June 8th
postcontent:
Do you want more training after your NRA Basic Pistol Course?
Do you want to shoot in a more dynamic setting?

10 student limit.

The Intermediate Pistol Course is all about getting comfortable with your firearm. This course will drive the core marksmanship fundamentals required to master the manipulation of your firearm. This course will take you out of the comfortable static shooting most people do at the local range. Emphasis is taken on instilling safety and proficiency with your firearm.
This course will prepare you to properly, safely and effectively unholster your firearm and present it to a threat if such need should arise. The dynamics of shooting at closer distances will be explained and the hands-on drills will drive home the importance of the core fundamentals.
This course is 25% classroom and 75% hands-on and will have you firing your handgun for approximately 6 hours. Manipulating your firearm under new pressures and timed constraints will prepare you for the unexpected. This course will not only teach you the skills, but will also give you the confidence you need to feel comfortable handling your firearm in worst case scenarios. This course is 1 day of hands-on lecture and hands-on drills.

title: For Sale:  Intermediate Pistol Class on June 8th
postcontent:
Do you want more training after your NRA Basic Pistol Course?
Do you want to shoot in a more dynamic setting?

10 student limit.

The Intermediate Pistol Course is all about getting comfortable with your firearm. This course will drive the core marksmanship fundamentals required to master the manipulation of your firearm. This course will take you out of the comfortable static shooting most people do at the local range. Emphasis is taken on instilling safety and proficiency with your firearm.
This course will prepare you to properly, safely and effectively unholster your firearm and present it to a threat if such need should arise. The dynamics of shooting at closer distances will be explained and the hands-on drills will drive home the importance of the core fundamentals.
This course is 25% classroom and 75% hands-on and will have you firing your handgun for approximately 6 hours. Manipulating your firearm under new pressures and timed constraints will prepare you for the unexpected. This course will not only teach you the skills, but will also give you the confidence you need to feel comfortable handling your firearm in worst case scenarios. This course is 1 day of hands-on lecture and hands-on drills.

title: For Sale:  Emergency Preparedness Medical supplies
postcontent:
Are you prepared? Sure you have your Defensive Tools, Ammo, Food Storage and BOB/GHB, but what does your First aid kit look like? Are you prepared to treat arterial bleeding? Do you have the supplies to treat a chest puncture or severed or mangled limb? In the times we live in we never know what we could potentially encounter. Get prepared and be ready. 

For Sale are 
20 x C.A.T (combat application tourniquet) 
20 x HyFin chest seals (for sucking chest wounds resulting from penetration of the upper thoracic cavity)
30 x QuickClot Combat Gauze.

Looking for $10 each piece. Minimum of 10 pieces if I am shipping. If you want me to ship add $10 for shipping. For shipments I will accept a USPS or Moneygram Money order.

Now yes I know that the expiration date on QC Gauze is 6/14, but I called the guys at 
Z-Medica Corporation and they explained that the active ingredient is inorganic and except for it being very hydroscopic is relatively inert. Nothing to age out. Other than the packaging which with prolonged exposure to UV light and or constant molesting could damage it. The contents will last 10 years or better.  The FDA requires an expiration date on ALL medical devices, medicines and supplies. And thinking about it, it also helps the manufacturers bottom line.... Making money. Now you can buy from the source and have a warm fuzzy feeling for $35-45 apiece or be smart and buy from me. 

Do your research and see what others are selling for. 
Since a few people have asked, I will accept $500 for all plus shipping which is about $30

title: For Sale:  Precision Rem 700 custom
postcontent: This rifle was built by red hawk custom shop in Colorado. It is a Remington 700 action with a 26" bull barrel cambered in 7mm-08. The 7mm-08 is a cartridge born from the 308 necked down to .284. There are a few great advantages to this the bullets used will have a higher BC( ballistic coefficient ). Which means the bullet flies farther, straighter, truer, greater velocity, high energy, and less recoil. It is ballistically far superior to the .308. I was able to shoot 3/4 moa with un-tuned loads very easily this is a 1/2 moa gun at 100 yards easily. It is set in a bell and Carlson A5 completely adjustable stock comb height, length of pull, and cant. Red hawk also installed a badger ordinance enlarged bolt knob, a talley 20 moa picatinny scope mount, lapped the bolt lugs, and tuned the trigger. This action is slick has been well taken care has only had 200 down the pipe. It comes with 1lb of imr4350, 40 rds of ammo, a set of RCBS dies, and assorted bullets. If it don't sell this weekend it is coming off the market thank you.

title: For Sale:  High prices? Keep more of your $$$
postcontent:
Some of the prices listed here are ridiculous. You use the internet to make a posting, take 2 mins to search the firearm you are selling. I can't count how many people have their used firearms listed for the same price or even higher than msrp. Then they wonder why no one wants to buy it and continually post it over and over.

Sites like slickguns.com will give you the prices that many of the major gun stores and online gun stores charge all in one simple search. You get a list of them all and the price they charge. It also listing shipping charges if someone wants to order online. You can even feel free to add $30 for ffl transfer(what most local shops charge) to that price. Maybe you overpaid because you didn't do any research and bought a firearms from the most expensive place in town, just don't expect hardly anyone to overpay because you got taken by an overpriced store.

$300-350 pistol brand new....and you want $450? Firearms hold their value well, but a used firearm is not worth the same amount or more than it costs brand new(antique and rare firearms excluded).

Maybe you'll get lucky and find some dumb schmuck who has never used the search bar of the internet or walked into a gun store before making a purchase, but chances are you will be laughed at, mocked, and will not make a sale. If someone is willing to pay that overly high asking price, you have to ask yourself why they are willing to pay more for a private sale? Maybe because they can't legally purchase the firearm cheaper at a store? Maybe you shouldn't be selling to them in the first place.

Just use a little common sense and take 2mins to do some research.

A true comparison is with the Russian Tiger Draganov. Having made a reputation for accuracy, this heavy duty barrel not found on most other rifles has chrome lined chamber and bore. This Vepr system along with excellent quality of all parts, to many to list here, has earned a legendary reputation for total dependability from the jungles to Siberia!
